DateAndTime.name: DateAndTime
DateAndTime.description: A date-time specification identical to rfc 1443 definition. field octets contents range ----- ------ -------- ----- 1 1-2 year 0..65536 2 3 month 1..12 3 4 day 1..31 4 5 hour 0..23 5 6 minutes 0..59 6 7 seconds 0..60 (use 60 for leap-second) 7 8 deci-seconds 0..9 For example, Tuesday May 26, 2003 at 1:30:15 PM EDT would be displayed as: 2003-5-26,13:30:15.0

ReadWrite.name: ReadWrite
ReadWrite.description: A textual convention for describing objects that enable or disable some sort of write access.

h150eSysState.name: h150eSysState
h150eSysState.description: The actual error state of the device. Contains the highest severity level of the recent error events. This object is updated automatically, but it can also be modified manually.

tftpSwitchoverDateTime.name: tftpSwitchoverDateTime
tftpSwitchoverDateTime.description: Date and time for the switchover to the new system software. The configured time will be ignored, if the upgrade is started with the downloadAndImmediateSwitchover define of the tftpDownloadAction object. octet format: field octets contents range hex (range dez) ----- ------ -------- --------- ---------- 1 1-2 year 00 00 - FF FF (0 - 65536) 2 3 month 01 - 0C (1 - 12) 3 4 day 01 - 1F (1 - 31) 4 5 hour 00 - 17 (0 - 23) 5 6 minutes 00 - 3B (0 - 59) 6 7 seconds 00 - 3B (0 - 60) 7 8 deci-seconds 00 - 09 (0 - 9) For example, to configure Wednesday June 16, 1999 at 8:30:15 AM would be configured as 07 cf 06 10 08 1E 0F 00

tftpDownloadAction.name: tftpDownloadAction
tftpDownloadAction.description: When this object is set to downloadAndImmediateSwitchover (2), the device will download the new software from the configured host. After the download is finished, the device will automatically restart with the new software. If downloadAndDelayedSwitchover (3) is specified, the new image is copied to the device. When the tftpDateTime value is matched, the device discontinues its normal operation and does the software switchover. After an automatic reset, it starts with the new system software. Setting downloadWithoutSwitchover (4) initiates a download without switching over to the new software. When the device is not downloading, this object will have a value of notDownloading(1).

h150eResetControl.name: h150eResetControl
h150eResetControl.description: Setting this object to warmBoot(2) causes the device to restart the application software with current configuration parameters saved in non-volatile memory. When the device is running normally, this variable has a value of running(1). The effect of configuring this object is identical to the configuration of the probeResetControl object of RFC 2021, except for the coldBoot option which is not supported.

h150eSwitchoverState.name: h150eSwitchoverState
h150eSwitchoverState.description: The values readyForSwitchover (1) and notReadyForSwitchover (2) indicate whether the system is ready to be switched over to the new software that was downloaded to the shadow flash area, or not. If it is not passible, h150eShadowFlashState gives details on the reason. Setting this object to switchoverNow (3) causes the device to switchover immediately to the new software which was downloaded to the shadow flash area before and restart the system. initSwitchoverDelayed(4) causes a delayed switchover.

h150eShadowFlashState.name: h150eShadowFlashState
h150eShadowFlashState.description: This object informs about the state of the shadow flash memory area which is used to buffer a new software image that is being downloaded to the system. A download is only possible when the state is flashDeleted (1). It is not possible to download if the state is flashNotDeleted(2), nor if it's flashWriteProtected(3) (this means it is internally locked by software because the system is not in the state of accepting new flash data). If the flash memory is smaller than 8 MB ( flashTooSmall(4) ), no transfer is possible, too. It is possible to delete an inactive software image from the shadow flash area by setting deleteFlashNow (5).

h150eLoadLevel.name: h150eLoadLevel
h150eLoadLevel.description: The actual CPU load level (per cent).

h150eTrapRepetitions.name: h150eTrapRepetitions
h150eTrapRepetitions.description: The number of trap repetitions for error events marked as very important (log-and-multiple-trap).

h150eCdrBufferState.name: h150eCdrBufferState
h150eCdrBufferState.description: Use this object to delete the CDR buffer.

h150eLogBufferState.name: h150eLogBufferState
h150eLogBufferState.description: Use this object to delete the log data.

numberOfErrorHistoryEntries.name: numberOfErrorHistoryEntries
numberOfErrorHistoryEntries.description: Contains the number of errors to be found in the error history table. This value can be used to delete the last x entries (reduce value by x) or to delete all entries (value = 0).

h150eErrorHistoryTable.name: h150eErrorHistoryTable
h150eErrorHistoryTable.description: This table contains information about the errors that occured.

h150eErrorIndex.name: h150eErrorIndex
h150eErrorIndex.description: Identification of an table entry enabled by this index.

h150eErrorClass.name: h150eErrorClass
h150eErrorClass.description: Contains the error class number (type of trap).

h150eAccessSlot.name: h150eAccessSlot
h150eAccessSlot.description: Contains the access slot for the error.

h150eAccessPort.name: h150eAccessPort
h150eAccessPort.description: Contains the local access port of the error. Local means that port numbering starts with 0 for each card.

h150eErrorSeverity.name: h150eErrorSeverity
h150eErrorSeverity.description: Contains the severity of the specific error.

sysHardwareVersion.name: sysHardwareVersion
sysHardwareVersion.description: Contains the version string of the system hardware.

sysSoftwareVersion.name: sysSoftwareVersion
sysSoftwareVersion.description: Contains the version string of the system software.

sysCodeNumber.name: sysCodeNumber
sysCodeNumber.description: Contains the code number of the system software.

sysSoftwareLocation.name: sysSoftwareLocation
sysSoftwareLocation.description: Contains location (address space) where the system software is currently running.

numberOfSlotTableEntries.name: numberOfSlotTableEntries
numberOfSlotTableEntries.description: Contains the number of entries in the slot table.

h150eSlotTable.name: h150eSlotTable
h150eSlotTable.description: This table contains information about the system slots.

cardIndex.name: cardIndex
cardIndex.description: Identification of an table entry enabled by this index.

cardBoxNum.name: cardBoxNum
cardBoxNum.description: Index of the box where the card is placed.

cardSlotNum.name: cardSlotNum
cardSlotNum.description: Index of the slot where the card is placed.

cardType.name: cardType
cardType.description: Code for the type of the card.

cardCodeNumber.name: cardCodeNumber
cardCodeNumber.description: Contains the code number of the card software.

cardState.name: cardState
cardState.description: Contains the state of the card.

numberOfPortTableEntries.name: numberOfPortTableEntries
numberOfPortTableEntries.description: Contains the number of entries in the port table.

h150ePortTable.name: h150ePortTable
h150ePortTable.description: This table contains information about the system ports.

portIndex.name: portIndex
portIndex.description: Identification of an table entry enabled by this index.

portCardIndex.name: portCardIndex
portCardIndex.description: Reference to the card the port is assigned to.

portType.name: portType
portType.description: Contains the type of the port.

portState.name: portState
portState.description: Contains the general state of the port.

portLock.name: portLock
portLock.description: This object contains the lock state of the port. A software lock can be enabled / disabled. Possible state transitions: unlocked -> lockedBySoftware lockedByHardware -> lockedBySoftAndHardware lockedBySoftware -> unlocked lockedBySoftAndHardware -> lockedByHardware

numberOfExtensionTableEntries.name: numberOfExtensionTableEntries
numberOfExtensionTableEntries.description: Contains the number of entries in the hardware extension table.

h150eExtensionTable.name: h150eExtensionTable
h150eExtensionTable.description: This table contains information about the hardware extensions.

extensionIndex.name: extensionIndex
extensionIndex.description: Identification of an table entry enabled by this index.

extensionDescription.name: extensionDescription
extensionDescription.description: Contains a textual desription of the hardware extension.

extensionCodeNumber.name: extensionCodeNumber
extensionCodeNumber.description: Contains the code number of the hardware extension.

numberOfLanConnTableEntries.name: numberOfLanConnTableEntries
numberOfLanConnTableEntries.description: Contains the number of entries in the LAN connection table.

h150eLanConnTable.name: h150eLanConnTable
h150eLanConnTable.description: This table contains information about the interfaces available for LAN access of the device or its cards.

lanConnIndex.name: lanConnIndex
lanConnIndex.description: Identification of an table entry enabled by this index.

lanConnDescription.name: lanConnDescription
lanConnDescription.description: Textual desription on the LAN connection.

lanConnIpAddress.name: lanConnIpAddress
lanConnIpAddress.description: IP address of the LAN connection.

lanConnSubnetMask.name: lanConnSubnetMask
lanConnSubnetMask.description: Subnet mask of the LAN connection.

hiPathAllServeServerIpAddress.name: hiPathAllServeServerIpAddress
hiPathAllServeServerIpAddress.description: IP address of the HiPath AllServe (Venus) server.

indexOfLastPortStatusNotificationTrap.name: indexOfLastPortStatusNotificationTrap
indexOfLastPortStatusNotificationTrap.description: Index of last 'port status change' notification trap sent by the device. Note: only reset possible (0)

sysSnmpAgentVersion.name: sysSnmpAgentVersion
sysSnmpAgentVersion.description: Version number of the systems SNMP agent (formatting: x.y.z.)

sysShadowSoftwareVersion.name: sysShadowSoftwareVersion
sysShadowSoftwareVersion.description: Contains the version string of the inactive (shadow) system software. This is the software image that has been transferred to the system without triggering the software switchover afterwards.

sysHiPathSymbolSubInfo.name: sysHiPathSymbolSubInfo
sysHiPathSymbolSubInfo.description: Contains an URL to detailed symbol information in addition to the symbol information contained in the common mib object deviceSymbolInfo.

sysHiPathBranding.name: sysHiPathBranding
sysHiPathBranding.description: Contains the branding string of the device.

numberOfFeatureStatTableEntries.name: numberOfFeatureStatTableEntries
numberOfFeatureStatTableEntries.description: Contains the number of feature counters to be found in the table.

h150eFeatureStatTable.name: h150eFeatureStatTable
h150eFeatureStatTable.description: This table contains information about the usage of specific system features. It is designed to monitor the use of these features for a limited time only, because each counter is limited to one byte.

featureIndex.name: featureIndex
featureIndex.description: Identification of an table entry enabled by this index.

featureCounter.name: featureCounter
featureCounter.description: This Counter indicates how often the feature was used since last system reload

featureStatTableReset.name: featureStatTableReset
featureStatTableReset.description: Enables reset (2) of all counters of the featureStatTable.

h150eCdrSeparator.name: h150eCdrSeparator
h150eCdrSeparator.description: Separator between following CDRs: DOS mode (1): CRLF UNIX mode (2): LF

h150eCdrElementSeparator.name: h150eCdrElementSeparator
h150eCdrElementSeparator.description: Separator between the different elements of one CDR: pipe (0x7c): '|' semicolon (0x3b): ';' blank (0x20): ' ' NOTE: no write access for blank

h150eCdrThresholdValue.name: h150eCdrThresholdValue
h150eCdrThresholdValue.description: CDR buffer limit (only relevant for TFTP server mode): threshold value (in percent) for sending a CDR data notification trap recommended values: 0 to 80

h150eCdrTftpFileCounter.name: h150eCdrTftpFileCounter
h150eCdrTftpFileCounter.description: CDR <FileCounter> (only relevant for TFTP client mode): For each transferred CDR-file a new filename is necassary filename: 'GDS<IPAdr>.c<FileCounter>'

h150eCdrTftpServerDestAddress.name: h150eCdrTftpServerDestAddress
h150eCdrTftpServerDestAddress.description: Destination IP addresse of CDR TFTP server (only relevant for TFTP client mode)

h150eCdrTftpServerAlternateDestAddress.name: h150eCdrTftpServerAlternateDestAddress
h150eCdrTftpServerAlternateDestAddress.description: Alternate destination IP addresse of CDR TFTP server (only relevant for TFTP client mode): is the CDR TFTP Server not reachable the switch transfers CDR data to this alternative server

h150eCdrTftpClientTimer.name: h150eCdrTftpClientTimer
h150eCdrTftpClientTimer.description: cycle time in minutes for initiating CDR output, max value 1439 minutes (23hours,59minutes) (only relevant for TFTP client mode)

h150eCdrTcpServerDestAddress.name: h150eCdrTcpServerDestAddress
h150eCdrTcpServerDestAddress.description: Destination IP addresse of CDR TCP server (only relevant for TCP client mode)

h150eCdrTcpServerDestPort.name: h150eCdrTcpServerDestPort
h150eCdrTcpServerDestPort.description: Destination TCP port of CDR TCP server (only relevant for TCP client mode)

h150eCdrOutputMode.name: h150eCdrOutputMode
h150eCdrOutputMode.description: CDR (Call Detailed Record) output mode: V24-Port (1): the PABX is permanently connected over a V.24 connection to an extern application and sends each CDR immidiatly NOTE: no write access UPN-Port (2): the PABX is permanently connected over terminal adapter (PPM) connection to an extern application and sends each CDR immidiatly NOTE: no write access PCVPL-Port (3): the PEBX is permanently connected over a CorNet TS connection to an extern application (PCVPL) and sends each CDR immidiatly NOTE: no write access TFTP-Client (4): the PABX sends the collected CDRs to the administrated TFTP-Server TFTP-Server (5): an extern TFTP client can request the collected CDRs TCP-Client (6): the PABX is permanently connected to an extern TCP server and sends each CDR immidiatly NoOutput (7): no output for CDR

h150eIndexOfLastCdrNotificationTrap.name: h150eIndexOfLastCdrNotificationTrap
h150eIndexOfLastCdrNotificationTrap.description: Index of last CDR notification trap sent by device Note: only reset possible (0)

h150etypeOfLastCdrNotificationTrap.name: h150etypeOfLastCdrNotificationTrap
h150etypeOfLastCdrNotificationTrap.description: Type of last CDR notification trap sent by the the device: (1) : error - CDR buffer overflow (2) : warning - CDR buffer is filled up over 80% (3) : notification - administrateable CDR buffer threshold is reached -> extern TFTP client has to get the collected CDRs (4) : warning - TCP Client couldn't reach administrated server (5) : warning - TFTP Client couldn't reach administrated server (6) : warning - TFTP Client couldn't reach administrated alternative server

h150eDescriptionOfLastCdrNotificationTra.name: h150eDescriptionOfLastCdrNotificationTrap
h150eDescriptionOfLastCdrNotificationTra.description: Textual description of last CDR notification trap sent by the device

sendAlarm.name: sendAlarm
sendAlarm.description: If an error occurs, there will be checked if the errorClass is configured to trigger an immediate signalling. If so, a trap will be send to the management station containing the information shown above.

sendCdrNotification.name: sendCdrNotification
sendCdrNotification.description: The CDR notification trap is sent to trigger further actions by the management station, for instance download of CDR data.

sendPortStatusNotification.name: sendPortStatusNotification
sendPortStatusNotification.description: The 'port status change' notification trap is sent to trigger a polling of the port table by a management station. It indicates one or more changes in port states.

sendUmRelatedChangeNotification.name: sendUmRelatedChangeNotification
sendUmRelatedChangeNotification.description: This trap is sent (to UM proxy), as the system detects changes.

umNodeNumber.name: umNodeNumber
umNodeNumber.description: The node number of the system. Unique number identifying the PBX.

umSrsEnabled.name: umSrsEnabled
umSrsEnabled.description: Indicates whether the SRS feature flag of the machine is enabled or not. The small remote site flag is an overall flag of the system.

umNumberOfSubscriberEntries.name: umNumberOfSubscriberEntries
umNumberOfSubscriberEntries.description: Number of entries in subscriber table.

umSubscriberTable.name: umSubscriberTable
umSubscriberTable.description: This table contains information about all HFA-Clients available for UM-configuration.

umLogicalPortNumber.name: umLogicalPortNumber
umLogicalPortNumber.description: The logical port number of the subscriber.

umInternalCallNumber.name: umInternalCallNumber
umInternalCallNumber.description: The internal call number of the subscriber.

umDIDNumber.name: umDIDNumber
umDIDNumber.description: The DID number of the subscriber.

umE164Number.name: umE164Number
umE164Number.description: The E.164 call number of the subscriber.

umDisplayName.name: umDisplayName
umDisplayName.description: The display name of the subscriber.

umStationType.name: umStationType
umStationType.description: The type of the station. e.g. UP0, S0, HFA, ...

umPortStatus.name: umPortStatus
umPortStatus.description: The status of the logical port.

umClassOfService.name: umClassOfService
umClassOfService.description: Classes of service can be used to restrict external calls. The types of calls that can be made from each station are defined for this purpose.

umCfssTarget.name: umCfssTarget
umCfssTarget.description: The target for Call Forwarding for Station out of Service.

umNumberOfUnconfirmedTraps.name: umNumberOfUnconfirmedTraps
umNumberOfUnconfirmedTraps.description: Number of entries in the umUnconfirmedTrapTable. A trap is confirmed and as result removed from the table, when its entry in the table is requested in a GetRequest for the 1st time. Traps presented in the table are retried as long as a GetRequest arrives.

umUnconfirmedTrapTable.name: umUnconfirmedTrapTable
umUnconfirmedTrapTable.description: This table contains information about traps sent to UM-Proxy. The contained traps have not yet been confirmed.

umTrapIdentifier.name: umTrapIdentifier
umTrapIdentifier.description: Unique identifier of the trap. A SetRequest with value 0 removes the entry from the table. A value unequal to 0 is erroneous.

umTrapType.name: umTrapType
umTrapType.description: The type of trap sent. Startup traps are sent as the system resets. The 2 types of modify traps aim on distinguishing between modification that are subscriber- related and those that are global.

umTrapLogicalPortNumber.name: umTrapLogicalPortNumber
umTrapLogicalPortNumber.description: In case of a modifySubscriber-type trap, the logical port number that was the reason for the traps is presented here. For the other umTrapTypes, the content is undefined!

umNetworkElementKey.name: umNetworkElementKey
umNetworkElementKey.description: A key that uniquely identifies the node towards UM. For a HiPath 3000/5000 this would be the IP-address, A simulator should additionally provide the port.
